  		<div class="text">
  		
  	
  		<p><strong>The general dental practitioner:</strong></p>
		
<p>Dentists in general practice work with patients over the long term. 
<p>They will often see members of the same family and their relationships last many years. 
<p>They work with their patients to prevent and treat dental and oral disease.
<p> Dentists are part of a team that includes dental nurses, hygeneists and dental therapists. 
<p>They are often the professionals who see the first signs of serious oral conditions and will refer patients to specialists for treatment.  
<p>If patients present with very complex needs they will refer on to hospital consultants or other specialist dentists.</p>
 
    	
    	 
    	
 	
